import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['u', 'v']]
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='u', y='v')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between u and v?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['u'])
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='u', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['u'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of u?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='v', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['v'].mean(), color='red', label=f"Mean: {data['v'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of v?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['index'] = pd.to_datetime(data['index'], errors='coerce')
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='index', y='u', data=data)
    chart.set_title('What is the relationship between index and u?', wrap=True)
    return chart

chart = plot(data)
